[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":159},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix\u002F":145,"related:\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix\u002F":154},"\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F20220405\u002F1504568293\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":104,"date":126,"description":127,"extension":128,"lang":129,"meta":130,"navigation":131,"path":132,"readingMinutes":133,"seo":134,"standalone":135,"stem":136,"tags":137,"tldr":142,"updated":142,"url":143,"__hash__":144},"content\u002Fen\u002FTailwindCSS\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix.md","Fixing VSCode's \"Unknown at rule @tailwind\" Warning","4150568239",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":119},"minimark",[11,16,29,33,36,42,48,51,68,71,82,100,106,110],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,28],"p",{},"Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework with a lot of upsides, which is why so many people are picking it up and learning it. But in VSCode you'll often hit ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"Unknown at rule @tailwind",", ",[21,26,27],{},"Unknown at rule @apply",", and similar warnings. This post is just a quick note on how to fix them.",[12,30,32],{"id":31},"the-fix","The fix",[17,34,35],{},"Tailwind CSS works alongside PostCSS, and as a frontend dev you almost certainly use VSCode — which means you've probably seen this:",[17,37,38],{},[39,40],"img",{"alt":23,"src":41},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FKpv9XAG.png",[17,43,44],{},[39,45],{"alt":46,"src":47},"Unknown at rule @layer","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FyKNPdIj.png",[17,49,50],{},"It doesn't really affect development, and the Tailwind CSS docs even mention this:",[52,53,54],"blockquote",{},[17,55,56,57,24,60,63,64,67],{},"Tailwind CSS uses a lot of custom CSS at-rules like ",[21,58,59],{},"@tailwind",[21,61,62],{},"@apply",", and ",[21,65,66],{},"@screen",", and in many editors this can trigger warnings or errors where these rules aren't recognized.",[17,69,70],{},"In short, Tailwind CSS uses some custom CSS at-rules that editors don't recognize, so they show warnings or errors like:",[72,73,74,77,79],"ul",{},[75,76,23],"li",{},[75,78,27],{},[75,80,81],{},"Unknown at rule @layer\n...\netc.",[17,83,84,85,88,89,96,97,99],{},"Since you're using Tailwind CSS with PostCSS, you'll already have a ",[21,86,87],{},"postcss.config.js",". Just install the ",[90,91,95],"a",{"href":92,"rel":93},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=csstools.postcss",[94],"nofollow","PostCSS Language Support"," extension in VSCode, and the ",[21,98,23],{}," warning goes away.",[17,101,102],{},[39,103],{"alt":104,"src":105},"TailwindCSS","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FJAuiseU.png",[12,107,109],{"id":108},"references","References",[72,111,112],{},[75,113,114],{},[90,115,118],{"href":116,"rel":117},"https:\u002F\u002Ftailwindcss.com\u002Fdocs\u002Feditor-setup#intelli-sense-for-vs-code",[94],"Editor Setup",{"title":120,"searchDepth":121,"depth":121,"links":122},"",2,[123,124,125],{"id":14,"depth":121,"text":15},{"id":31,"depth":121,"text":32},{"id":108,"depth":121,"text":109},"2022-04-05 23:02:50","Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework with a lot of upsides, which is why so many people are picking it up. But in VSCode you often get \"Unknown at rule @tailwind\" or \"Unknown at rule @apply\" warnings — here's how to silence them.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix","1",{"title":6,"description":127},false,"en\u002FTailwindCSS\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix",[138,139,140,141],"Tailwind CSS","PostCSS","VSCode","Unknown",null,"\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fvscode-unknown-at-rule-tailwind-fix\u002F","LPir-fGwx8YAohc944jkRGvPQU4aUcC_2pQzA-P1amc",{"newer":146,"older":150},{"url":147,"title":148,"date":149},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F16\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-29-atlas-mongodb-connection\u002F","(29) The Frontend Dev Forced to Eat Mango - Connecting to Atlas MongoDB","2022-04-16 20:40:13",{"url":151,"title":152,"date":153},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F05\u002Fnodejs-mango-28-mongodb-compass-atlas-gui\u002F","The Frontend Dev Forced to Eat Mango (28): Browsing Your Atlas Database with MongoDB Compass","2022-04-05 22:30:31",[155],{"url":156,"title":157,"date":158,"readingMinutes":133},"\u002Fen\u002Ftailwindcss\u002F2022\u002F07\u002F02\u002Ftailwind-intellisense-vite-react-jsx\u002F","Making VSCode's Tailwind CSS IntelliSense Work With React JSX","2022-07-02 21:32:31",1784010292895]